element_description: A complete, or near complete, insect or similar individual
Whole or partial pollen grain
Whole or partial leaf
An individual or partial sead grain
Minimum Number of Individuals - an estimation of the number of whole animals represented by the collective parts found.
Left wing case.
Right wing case.
Dorsal section of arthropod exoskeleton or shell, plus some vertebrates such as turtles.
Reproductive organ of male insect.
Foliage element of pine, spruce and other needle bearing plants.
Seed releasing body of coniferous plants.
Lower part of the leaf, sometimes surrounding the stem.
Place on a plant stem where a leaf is attached, solid stem part.
Place on a plant stem where a leaf is attached, hollow stem part.
Place on a plant stem where a leaf is attached, stem part indeterminate or both solid and hollow node parts.
Flowers of the grasses, cereals etc.
Broken lemmas, glumes etc. Commonly unwanted products of threshing.
A fragment part of a segment from the main axis of the cereal/grass spike to which the spikelets are attached.
Part(s) of the main axis of the cereal/grass spike to which the spikelets are attached.
Tree/bush/plant
Unidentified ~pollen sized fossil
Hard casing of nut, fruit stone or similar
Fruiting body (i.e. pulp and seed or seedless body, but not only seeds)
Over ground structural component of plant (note: use other terms for woody plant twigs, branches etc)
Small terminal branch of woody plant
Outermost layer of woody plant stem or root
Structural tissue of woody plant, e.g. wood chips or bits in soil samples (note: use twig for small branches)
Supporting and most commonly underground structural part of plant with the function of absorbing water and nutrients from the soil. (Variation in function and relation to ground occur).
Tuber/bulb-like structure on the roots of some cultivated plants (e.g. Arrhenatherum elatius var. bulbosum)
Individual plate on a cone
Internal part of seed, usually providing starch (nutrition) for the initial growth of the plant
Grassy cultivated plant (mainly cereal) stem(s)
